INSERT INTO items VALUES('https://locusmag.com/2024/01/around-the-web-lisa-tuttle-reviews-scott-edelman-dines-george-bass-recalls-octavia-butler/','Around the Web: Lisa Tuttle Reviews; Scott Edelman Dines; George Bass Recalls Octavia Butler',replace('<p><strong>The Guardian</strong>: Lisa Tuttle reviews Aliya Whiteley, Alice McIlroy, Esmie Jikiemi-Pearson, Emma Hinds, and Maud Woolf</p>\n<p><strong>Scott Edelman</strong> dines with Nina Kiriki Hoffman and Pat Murphy</p>\n<p><strong>Washington Post, 13 Jan 2024</strong>: A 1993 dystopian novel imagined the world in 2024. It’s eerily accurate. &#8212; George Bass on Octavia Butler&#8217;s &#8216;Parable of the Sower&#8217; <a href="https://locusmag.com/2024/01/around-the-web-lisa-tuttle-reviews-scott-edelman-dines-george-bass-recalls-octavia-butler/" class="read-more">...Read More </a></p>','\n',char(10)),NULL,'','2024-01-15 19:40:00','Locus Magazine','',NULL,'2024-01-15 20:00:28','saved');
INSERT INTO items VALUES('https://locusmag.com/2024/01/weekly-bestsellers-15-january-2024/','Weekly Bestsellers, 15 January 2024',replace('<div style="background-color: #dae1e8; padding: 14px 0px 0px 0px; text-align: center;">\n<p>Rebecca Ross&#8217;s <b>Ruthless Vows</b> (Wednesday Books) is #1 on the YA lists of both New York Times and Publishers Weekly this week.</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\nTitle\nDebut / #wks on any list\nNYT\n01.21\nLAT\n01.14\nUSAT \n01.07\nPW \n01.15\nAmz \n(01.15)\nUK:\nAmz UK \n(01.15)\nCanada:\nAmz.ca \n(01.15)\n\n\nItems on list -x- number of lists surveyed\n\n10&#215;3\n10&#215;2\n150\n15&#215;3\n100\n100\n100\n\n\nHardcovers\n\n\nAlderman, The Future\n01.15.24 / 1\n\n\n124 ++ <a href="https://locusmag.com/2024/01/weekly-bestsellers-15-january-2024/" class="read-more">...Read More </a>','\n',char(10)),NULL,'','2024-01-15 18:51:31','Locus Magazine','',NULL,'2024-01-15 20:00:28','saved');
INSERT INTO items VALUES('https://locusmag.com/2024/01/tom-purdom-1936-2024/','Tom Purdom (1936-2024)',replace('<p>SF writer Tom Purdom, 87, died January 14, 2024.</p>\n<p>Thomas Edward Purdom was born April 19, 1936 in New Haven CT, and lived in Philadelphia PA with his wife, Sara Wescoat Purdom. He began publishing SF with &#8220;Grief for a Man&#8221; (1957), and debut novel <strong>I Want the Stars</strong> appeared in 1964. Other books include <strong>The Tree Lord of Imeten</strong> (1966), <strong>Five Against Arlane</strong> (1967), <strong>Reduction in Arms</strong> (1971), and  <a href="https://locusmag.com/2024/01/tom-purdom-1936-2024/" class="read-more">...Read More </a></p>','\n',char(10)),NULL,'','2024-01-15 17:34:28','Locus Magazine','',NULL,'2024-01-15 20:00:28','saved');
INSERT INTO items VALUES('https://locusmag.com/2024/01/ai-jiang-where-the-ghosts-live/','Ai Jiang: Where the Ghosts Live',replace('<p></p>\n<p><strong>AI JIANG</strong> was born June 18, 1997 in Fujian, China, and emigrated to Canada with her family at age four. She attended the University of Toronto, the Humber School for Writers, and the Gotham Writers’ Workshop, and earned her MFA in creative writing from the University of Edinburgh in 2022.</p>\n<p>She began publishing work of genre interest with “Hello’’ (2021) in The Dark, and more than 35 stories have since  <a href="https://locusmag.com/2024/01/ai-jiang-where-the-ghosts-live/" class="read-more">...Read More </a></p>','\n',char(10)),NULL,'','2024-01-15 16:30:12','Locus Magazine','',NULL,'2024-01-15 20:00:28','saved');
INSERT INTO items VALUES('https://locusmag.com/2024/01/new-books-16-january-2023/','New Books: 16 January 2023',replace('<p>Avery, Amy: <b>The Longest Autumn</b>\n(Macmillan/Flatiron 9781250896490, $28.99, 320pp, formats: hardcover, ebook, audio, 01/16/2024)</p>\n<p>Fantasy mystery romance novel. Seasons stop turning when the mortal Time and the god of Autumn are trapped in the mortal world, and the two are torn between the need to fix things and their forbidden attraction to each other. A first novel.</p>\n<p>&#160;</p>\n<p>Bertino, Marie-Helene: <b>Beautyland</b>\n(Macmillan/Farrar, Straus, Giroux 9780374109288, $28, 336pp, formats: hardcover, ebook,  <a href="https://locusmag.com/2024/01/new-books-16-january-2023/" class="read-more">...Read More </a></p>','\n',char(10)),NULL,'','2024-01-16 16:09:53','Locus Magazine','',NULL,'2024-01-16 16:10:15','saved');
INSERT INTO items VALUES('https://locusmag.com/2024/01/2024-writers-prize-shortlist/','2024 Writers’ Prize Shortlist',replace('<p>The Writers&#8217; Prize, formerly the Rathbones Folio Prize, announced shortlists in three categories: Non-Fiction, Fiction, and Poetry. Titles or authors of genre interest include <strong>The Fraud</strong> by Zadie Smith (Penguin) for Fiction.</p>\n<p>Winners will be announced March 13, 2024 at the London Book Fair. Each category winner receives £2,000 and the winner of the Writers&#8217; Prize Book of the Year will receive £30,000.</p>\n<div class="mynomorebulletlist">\n<p>For more information, including the complete shortlists, </p></div> <a href="https://locusmag.com/2024/01/2024-writers-prize-shortlist/" class="read-more">...Read More </a>','\n',char(10)),NULL,'','2024-01-16 00:03:06','Locus Magazine','',NULL,'2024-01-16 16:10:15','saved');
INSERT INTO items VALUES('https://locusmag.com/2024/01/howard-waldrop-1946-2024/','Howard Waldrop (1946-2024)',replace('<p>Author Howard Waldrop, 77, died January 14, 2024. Waldrop was one of our most accomplished and celebrated authors of short fiction, known for his erudite, playful, and allusive work. His most famous story, &#8220;The Ugly Chickens&#8221; (1980), won World Fantasy and Nebula Awards, and was a Hugo Award finalist.</p>\n<p>Waldrop&#8217;s first work of genre interest was &#8220;Lunchbox&#8221; in Analog (1972), and he went on to publish scores of stories, including  <a href="https://locusmag.com/2024/01/howard-waldrop-1946-2024/" class="read-more">...Read More </a></p>','\n',char(10)),NULL,'','2024-01-15 21:40:37','Locus Magazine','',NULL,'2024-01-16 16:10:15','saved');
